data.name: Stillness And Form Practice
data.description:
The Stillness and Form Practice are foundational components of the Fighting Monkey Practice. Our will focus on the Stillness Practice and it's many postures and on different parts of the Father Form.

Sessions are $10.

data.name: Morning Practice
data.description:
The Morning Practice is a multigenerational movement practice that uses play, tools, games, drills to develop our movement awareness and broaden our movement practice.

Each day we focus on a different aspect of the Fighting Monkey Practice.

data.name: Community MOVMNT Sessions
data.description:
The Community Movmnt Sessions are based on the Fighting Monkey Practice and provides opportunities to explore, research, and play with our movement patterns and see how they help and hurt us in our daily lives. The practice is about developing an understanding of our bodies and how we can build a practice that will support us in our lives and give us the tools to age well and in grace.


The focus of this class is to introduce and bring awareness to a different approach to fitness and how one can become fit, stay fit and promote a lifestyle that is counter to the modern approach to movement. This class is multi-generational and is open to all levels of athletic ability, from beginner to experienced. Everyone will be challenged, encouraged and supported in their movement research. We will explore movement through drills, games and partner work.


The group will meet on Wednesdays from 6:30-8 and sessions are completely free of charge.
